# Prisma conventions — backend

- Schema is the source of truth. Change `schema.prisma` first, then
  generate a migration — never hand-edit production DB outside migrations.
- Map table/column names with `@@map` / `@map` (snake_case in Postgres,
  camelCase in TypeScript).
- Prefer validated strings over Postgres enums when the frontend already
  owns a string-literal union (see `Lead.stage`).
- Seed scripts must be **idempotent** (skip or upsert; never blindly
  duplicate on every `docker compose up`).
- `tenantId` is a nullable placeholder — do not enforce or filter on it
  until auth lands.
- Keep domain tables owned by one module conceptually (`leads` vs
  `property_lookup_cache`); don't add FKs that couple the two domains.
